race.description: Taylors Hill Retirement Village Mdn Plate
race.comment: Lots of improvers out in journey. JAWSOME ROB (4) was placed fresh over a mile then safely held at the same trip but at Sandown Hillside. Much easier here, fitter again and extra trip a plus. Gets his chance. Likewise ZORB (12) who is fitter for two runs back and should appreciate this company. Much improved run second-up over 2000m and should give a sight. BUSH ETIQUETTE (9) has started just twice and improved out of sight when stepping up to a mile. Extra ground here is a big plus. WHATTA MAN (6) has raced three times and is yet another who looks suited stretching out further in journey. Likely to push forward off the wide draw. DIVINE CLEMENTINE (7) has placed two of three this campaign and went down fighting latest when beaten just over a length. Among the main hopes again.
